<body>
<h1>Final Review </h1>
<table width="100%" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top"><strong>Contracts &amp; UCC </strong></td>
        <td valign="top"><strong>Torts</strong></td>
        <td valign="top"><strong>Criminal</strong></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td width="25%" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Intro</strong></p>
                    <p>The rights and remedies of the parties depends on whether there was a valid contract.</p>
                    <p>A <strong>Contract</strong> is a promise or set of promises the performance of which the law will recognise as a duty and the breach of which the law will provide a remedy.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>A. FORMATION OF CONTRACTS </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Is UCC? </strong></p>
                    <p>a. UCC Article 2<br />
                    b. Sale of Goods: UCC<br />
                        c. Movable items at the time of K<br />
                        d. All other contracts: Common Law</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">UCC article 2 governs contracts for&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">sale of GOODS</strong>,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">movable things</strong>&nbsp;at the time of identification of the contract. Otherwise, only COMMON LAW governs the contract.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Are Parties Merchant? </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Person who trades in or holds himself out<br />
                    b. by occupation or knowledgable about the goods</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under the UCC, a Merchant is a person who</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;trades in</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;or otherwise&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">holds himself out&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">by occupation or otherwise&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">knowledgeable about the goods</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;of the contract. Further, a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">principal</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;that&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">employs</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">an&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">agent</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;that is a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">merchant</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;is held to be a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">merchant by implication.</strong></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Offer</strong></p>
                    <p>a. manifestation of present contractual intent;<br />
                        b. communicated to the offeree;<br />
                        c. with definite terms;<br />
                        d. objective person would believe that assent would form a bargain;</p>
                    <p><strong>Common law:</strong><br />
                        a. Qtips: quantity, time, identity of parties, price, subject matter;</p>
                    <p><strong>UCC:</strong><br />
                        a. Terms required are parties and quantity;</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under contract law, an OFFER is a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">manifestation</strong>&nbsp;of present contractual<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;intent communicated to the offeree</strong>&nbsp;such that an objective person would reasonably believe&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">assent would form a bargain</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">At common law, a communication was only deemed sufficient to constitute an offer if it specified the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">parties</strong>,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">subject matter</strong>,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">quantity</strong>,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">price</strong>, and the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">time</strong>&nbsp;of performance (<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">Q-tips</strong>&nbsp;- quantity, time, identity of parties, subject matter)</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">At UCC, the UCC deems a communication sufficient to constitute an offer if it specifies the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">parties</strong>and the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">quantity</strong>. The UCC provides &quot;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">GAP FILLERS</strong>&quot; that may be used by the court to determine any additional terms.</p>                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Mutual Assent </strong></p>
                    <p>a. offer posed by the offeror<br />
                        b. accepted by the offeree</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Merchant's Firm Offer </strong></p>
                    <p>a. ucc 2-205;<br />
                        b. offer by merchant;<br />
                        c. to leave offer open;<br />
                        d. for stated period or reasonable period (less than 3 months);<br />
                        e. in writing;<br />
                        f. cannot be revoked by offeror;<br />
                        g. offeree can accept even offeror has reovked the offer.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under UCC&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">2-205</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;an&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">offer by a merchant&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">that promises to &quot;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">leave the offer open</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&quot; for a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">period of time</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;cannot be revoked by the offeror if it is&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">stated in writing</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, for the period of time stated, or for a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">reasonable period</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;of time (given the circumstances) if no time period is stated. However, regardless of the period of time stated by the offeror, the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">offeror can revoke within 3 months</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;if that is less than the time period stated. If the merchant promises to &quot;leave the offer open&quot; for any period of time, whether more or less than 3 months, that is the &quot;reasonable period of time&quot; in which the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">offeree can accept the offer even if the offeror could legally revoke&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">the offer sooner.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Unilateral Contract </strong></p>
                    <p>a. offer that unequivocally indicates;<br />
                        b. acceptance by completion of the performance;</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the common law a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">UNILATERAL CONTRACT OFFER</strong>&nbsp;is one that&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">unequivocally</strong>&nbsp;indicates&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">acceptance</strong>&nbsp;can&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">only</strong>&nbsp;be manifested&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">by</strong>&nbsp;completion of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">performance</strong>&nbsp;by the offeree. GENERAL OFFERS, reward or bounty offers, are always unilateral contract offers.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Option Contract </strong></p>
                    <p>a. contractual agreement that;<br />
                        b. offeror will not revoke the offer;<br />
                        c. for specified period of time;<br />
                        d. in exchange for Consideration from the offeree;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under common law an&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">OPTION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;is a contractual agreement that an&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">offeror will not revoke an offer</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;for a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">specific period of time</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;in exchange for&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">CONSIDERATION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;from the offeree. </span> </p>
                    </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Acceptance</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>For Common Law</strong><br />
                        a. Under mirror image rule, <br />
                        b. acceptance is unequivocal assent to the terms of the offer.</p>
                    <p><strong>For UCC</strong><br />
                        a. under ucc 2-206<br />
                        b. not otherwise expressly conditioned<br />
                        c. in any reasonable manner<br />
                        d. including promise to ship or shipment of conforming or non conforming goods;<br />
                        e. shipment of non conforming goods as an express accomodation is not an acceptance;<br />
                        f. ucc 2-207, allows acceptance with varying terms</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the common law<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;MIRROR IMAGE RULE</strong>&nbsp;an acceptance is an&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">unequivocal assent</strong>&nbsp;to an offer.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">UCC 2-206</strong>&nbsp;an acceptance of an offer&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">not otherwise expressly conditioned</strong>&nbsp;may be&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">made in any REASONABLE MANNER</strong>, including a promise to ship or shipment of either conforming or non-conforming goods. BUT a shipment of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">NON-CONFORMING</strong>&nbsp;goods as an&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">EXPRESS ACCOMMODATION</strong>&nbsp;is not an acceptance. Further,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">UCC 2-207</strong>&nbsp;allows an&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">acceptance containing varying terms</strong>&nbsp;to be effective.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;                     </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Consideration</strong></p>
                    <p>a. exchange of promise;<br />
                        b. posing legal detriment;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">CONSIDERATION is an exchange of promises posing legal detriment such that the law deems it sufficient to support an agreement.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Varying Terms </strong></p>
                    <p>a. ucc 2-207<br />
                        b. contract between merchants<br />
                        c. offer did not expressly require acceptance based on varying terms<br />
                        d. offeror does not object within reasonable period of time or 10 days<br />
                        e. varying terms are not the material alteration of the terms of the contract</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under UCC 2-207 an acceptance that includes varying terms is still effective. If the contract is between merchants the varying term proposed by the offeree may become part of the contract if the offer did not&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">expressly require acceptance</strong>&nbsp;according to its terms, the<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;offeror does not object&nbsp;</strong>to the varying terms within a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">reasonable time</strong>, and the varying terms are&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">not a material alteration</strong>of the offer term.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">If the acceptance is&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">expressly conditioned on the varying terms</strong>&nbsp;by the offeree, the response is effectively a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">rejection</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">counter-offer</strong>. Otherwise the varying terms are considered only &quot;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">proposed modifications</strong>&quot;.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Even when varying terms do not automatically become part of the contract they may become part of the contract by agreement, and the UCC allows modification without additional consideration.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Offer lapsed </strong></p>
                    <p>a. offer lapse in a reasonable period of time;<br />
                        b. cannot be accepted after it lapses;</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">An offer must be accepted before it LAPSES. Unless there is an option, an offer lapses in the time stated or if no time is stated within a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">reasonable time&nbsp;</strong>after the offer is made.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under common law an offer&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">LAPSES AND CANNOT BE ACCEPTED</strong>&nbsp;unless it is accepted in a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">reasonable period of time</strong>. Oral offers are deemed to lapse at the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">end of the conversation</strong>, and written offers are deemed to lapse within the timeframe implied by the means of dispatch, absent contrary agreement or implication.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Effective Acceptance </strong></p>
                    <p>a. acceptance effective on dispatch<br />
                        b. dispatched in the manner specified;<br />
                        c. or same or faster means if not specified</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the MAILBOX RULES of the common law an<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;acceptance is effective when dispatched</strong>, if dispatched in the<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;manner specified</strong>&nbsp;in the offer, or by the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">same or faster means&nbsp;</strong>the offer was transmitted where the offer does not specify a means of communication.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">Rejection</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">Revocation</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Effective Rejection </strong></p>
                    <p>a. rejection upon receipt<br />
                        b. acceptance effective upon dispatch<br />
                        exception:<br />
                        c. offeror changes position in reliance of communication of rejection; not knowing acceptance is dispatch first<br />
                        d. then we have rejection regardless of the fact that acceptance is dispatched first.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under the</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;MAILBOX RULES</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;of contract law a rejection is&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">effective upon receipt</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;while an acceptance may be effective upon dispatch. An EXCEPTION is made if the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">OFFEROR CHANGES POSITION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;in reliance upon a communication of rejection,&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">not knowing that an acceptance was dispatched</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;prior to receipt of the rejection. In that case the rejection is effective upon receipt regardless of the fact an acceptance was also dispatched.</span> </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Effective Revocation </strong></p>
                    <p>a. revocation effective upon receipt</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">MAILBOX RULES</strong>&nbsp;revocation of a contract offer is usually<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;effective upon receipt</strong>.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Implied in Fact </strong></p>
                    <p>a. no express contract between the parties;<br />
                        b. one party bestow benefit on other;<br />
                        c. reasonably expecting it to be compensated;<br />
                        d. other party knowingly accept those benefits;<br />
                        e. knowingly other party expects to be compensated.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Is Writing Needed (SOF)</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Under Common law, </strong><br />
                    a. certain types of the contract must be written to be legally enforced;<br />
                        b. they are MY LEG: marriage, year, land, executor, gurantor;</p>
                    <p><strong>Under UCC</strong><br />
                        a. sale of goods more than 500;</p>
                    <p><strong>Between Merchants</strong><br />
                        a. sales confirmation with quantity will bind both parties;<br />
                        b. if not objected in 10 days;</p>
                    <p><strong>Exceptions: sof not for following</strong><br />
    a. special made goods;<br />
    b. partial performance;<br />
    c. admission that contract exists;<br />
                    </p>
                    <p><strong>Under 2-209</strong>, modification must also be in writing else it is not enforced.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">If ONLY common law governs say,</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the STATUTE OF FRAUDS&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">certain types of contracts must be written</strong>&nbsp;in order to be&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">legally enforced</strong>, and one type is a contract for (pick one if it applies here -- MARRIAGE, more than a YEAR, LAND, EXECUTOR of an estate, GUARANTEE of a debt).</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">MYLEG</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">If UCC say,</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under UCC 2-201, a contract for sale of goods worth $500 or more must evidenced by a writing sufficient to show the existence of a contract and signed by the party against whom the contract is to be enforced. But between merchants a SALES CONFIRMATION by one listing quantity will bind both parties if the receiving party does not object within 10 days.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Elements:</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">1. Certain contracts must be in written (for legal enforcement)</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">2. MY LEGS : Marriage, more than Year, Land, Executor, Goods/Gurantee, Surety.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">3. UCC sale of goods more than 500</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">4. Between merchants, sales confirmation with quantity will bind both parties.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">5. If not objected in 10 days</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Furthermore, the UCC provides exceptions for SPECIAL MADE GOODS, where there is an ADMISSION by the party to be bound that there had been an agreement, or where there has been PARTIAL PERFORMANCE of the contract (i.e. acceptance of some or all goods or payment).</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under UCC 2-209 contract modifications must be written to be legally enforceable if the contract, as modified, is for over $500. Otherwise modification agreements will be treated as waivers of conditions that can be always be retracted, unless the Court estops retraction to prevent injustice.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>B. CONTRACT TERMS </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Contract Terms in Common Law</strong></p>
                    <p>a. Qtips: quantity, time, identity of parties, price, subject matter;</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Contract Terms in UCC </strong></p>
                    <p>                    a. Terms required are parties and quantity;</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Timely Performance </strong></p>
                    <p>a. parties agree at the time of the contract;<br />
                        b. that timely performance is material condition;<br />
                        c. then it is called express condition;<br />
                        d. and contract is called Time is Essense;</p>
                    <p><strong>Time performance as implied material condition</strong><br />
                        a. if parties know tardy performance will deny the benefit of bargain;</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;                                                    </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Buyer Satisfaction </strong></p>
                    <p>a. reasonable satisfactory performance is always an implied material condition;<br />
                        b. parties may agree that buyer satisfaction is material condition;<br />
                        c. then buyers who are not satisfied are not legally bound to pay;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under contract law reasonably satisfactory performance by the parties is ALWAYS AN IMPLIED MATERIAL CONDITON of every contract. However, the parties may agree that buyer&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">SATISFACTION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">is a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">MATERIAL CONDITION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;so buyers who are&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">not actually satisfied</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;have&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">no legal duty to pay</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Parol Evidence Rule </strong></p>
                    <p>a. evidence of prior or contemporaneuous agreement;<br />
                        b. may not be introduced to vary or conflict;<br />
                        c. to the terms of the fully integrated writing;<br />
                        d. unless it shows evidence of DAM FOIL<br />
                        e. i.e. duress, ambiguity, mistake, fraud, oral condition precedent, illegality, lack of consideration</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">(This is only an issue if there is a detailed written contract. This and the Statute of Frauds can almost never both be issues in the same fact pattern because usually the contract can only be either written or oral, not both at the same time.)</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the PAROL EVIDENCE RULE evidence of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">PRIOR or CONTEMPORANEOUS</strong>&nbsp;agreements may not be introduced to&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">VARY or CONTRADIC</strong>T the terms of a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">FULLY INTEGRATED WRITING</strong>&nbsp;unless it is to show evidence of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">[DAM FOIL</strong>] Duress, Ambiguity, Mistake, Fraud, Oral condition precedent, Illegality, or Lack of consideration.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Requirement Contract </strong></p>
                    <p>a. buy or sell &quot;all the needed amount&quot; by the buyer;<br />
                        b. during stated period of time;<br />
                        c. quantity is actually needed by the buyer during stated time;<br />
                        d. not more than reasonably proportionate than the previous one.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">A requirements contract offer is one that offers to buy or sell &quot;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">all needed amounts</strong>&quot; by the buyer during a stated period of time.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The &quot;quantity&quot; of the contract is the amount actually needed by the buyer during the stated period, but not more than reasonably proportionate to amounts previously needed. (UCC 2-306)</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">A valid requirements contract offer must bind the buyer to purchase All amounts needed from the seller and cannot be just for amounts &quot;ordered&quot; or &quot;wanted&quot;.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Output Contract </strong></p>
                    <p>a. buy or sell &quot;all output&quot; produced by the seller;<br />
                        b. during stated period of time;<br />
                        c. quantity actually produced by the seller;<br />
                        d. not more than reasonably proportionate to previous one.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">An output contract offer is one that offers to buy or sell &quot;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">all output</strong>&quot; produced by the seller during a stated period of time.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The &quot;quantity&quot; of the contract is the amount actually produced by the seller during the stated period, but not more than reasonably proportionate to amounts previously produced (UCC 2-306)</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Condition Precedent, Concurrent, Subsequent </strong></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>C. DEFENSES </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Lack of Intent </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Objective main rule;<br />
                        b. <strong>intent</strong> to enter into the contract;<br />
                        c. if <strong>objective observer </strong>concluded from the <strong>communication</strong>;<br />
                        d. that <strong>assent</strong> would form a bargain;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">OBJECTIVE MAN RULE</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, there is sufficient&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">INTENT to enter into a contract</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;if an objective observer listening to the parties would have reasonably concluded from their communications that assent would form a bargain.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Lack of Consideration </strong></p>
                    <p>a. modification of contract;<br />
                        b. must be supported by consideration;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under contract law every valid contract, and&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">any modification of a contract</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, must be supported by&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">CONSIDERATION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, a BARGAINED FOR exchange posing sufficient LEGAL DETRIMENT that the law will enforce the agreement.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Contract Modification </strong></p>
                    <p>a. ucc 2-209<br />
                        b. contract modification do not require consideration;<br />
                        c. but must be supported by sufficient writing;<br />
                        d. under 2-201, modification without sufficient writing is not enforceable;</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under UCC 2-209 contract&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">modifications</strong>&nbsp;do&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">not require consideration</strong>, but if a contract as modified would have to be&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">supported by a sufficient writing</strong>&nbsp;under UCC 2-201, and the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">modification is not supported by a writing</strong>, it is&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">not enforceable</strong>&nbsp;at law.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Unconsionable </strong></p>
                    <p>a. no reasonable finding of intent;<br />
                        b. so unconsionable contracts are not enforceable;</p>
                    <p><strong>Adhesion Contract:</strong><br />
                        a. take it or leave it are not enforceable;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under contract law an&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">unconscionable contract will not be enforceable</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;because there is&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">NO REASONABLE FINDING OF INTENT</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to enter into such a contract. An&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">ADHESION CONTRACT&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">is a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&quot;take it or leave it&quot;&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">contract that a party is forced to agree to, and it will often be found unenforceable.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Duress </strong></p>
                    <p>a. good faith agreement are enforceable;<br />
                        b. illegal threat's are not valid;<br />
                        c. acts to create threat of economic harm are not enforceable;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under contract law only&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">good faith agreements are enforceable</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">. No contract agreement induced by&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">illegal threats</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;is valid. Likewise, agreements induced by deliberate&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">acts to create threats of economic harm are not enforceable</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Fraud </strong></p>
                    <p>a. party has duty to reveal facts;<br />
                        b. party deliberately concealing the facts;<br />
                        c. or misrepresenting the facts;<br />
                        d. if party seeking to void the contract;<br />
                        e. would have not agreed to bargain;<br />
                        f. but for the concealment or misrepresentation;</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under contract law FRAUD is a defense to enforcement of a contract where a party 1)&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">deliberately misrepresented material facts</strong>, 2) the party raising the defense reasonably&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">relied on the misrepresentations</strong>, and 3) the party to be bound&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">would not have entered</strong>&nbsp;into the contract&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">but for the misrepresentation</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under contract law a contract induced through deliberate&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">CONCEALMENT of material facts</strong>&nbsp;by a party with a duty to reveal the facts, or by a party deliberately concealing and/or&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">MISREPRESENTING</strong>&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">material facts</strong>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">unenforceable</strong>&nbsp;if it can be shown the party seeking to void the contract would&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">never have agreed to the bargain but for the concealment and/or misrepresentation</strong>.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Incapacity</strong></p>
                    <p>a. Contract cannot be forced against who lacks capacity;<br />
                        b. exception: provision of necessities of life;<br />
                        c. if legal capacity is removed, he has to repudiate the contract within reasonable time;<br />
                        d. or else have to affirm it;</p>
                    <p>a. party lacking the capacity can enforce the contract against the party that does not lack.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under contract law a contract cannot be enforced&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">AGAINST</strong>&nbsp;one who&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">lacks capacity</strong>.&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">EXCEPTIONS</strong>are contracts for provision of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">NECESSITIES of life</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under contract law a contract,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">except</strong>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">necessities of life</strong>,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">cannot</strong>&nbsp;be&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">enforced</strong>&nbsp;at law against a party which&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">lacked legal capacity</strong>&nbsp;at the time of execution. But if a legal incapacity is&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">removed</strong>&nbsp;the party to be bound must&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">repudiate the contract within a reasonable period</strong>&nbsp;of time or they will be&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">deemed to have affirmed or ratified it</strong>. The period of time in which a party gaining legal capacity must repudiate a contract may be set by statue.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">A party lacking capacity can enforce a contract against a party that does not lack capacity.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp;                      </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Illegality </strong></p>
                    <p>a. contract cannot be enforced for illegal purpose.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under contract law, a contract generally cannot be enforced by a party who knowingly&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">entered</strong>&nbsp;into it for an<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;illegal purpose</strong>.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Impossibility </strong></p>
                    <p>a. performance of contract duties must be possible at the time of contract;<br />
                        b. if <strong>performance becomes impossible</strong>;<br />
                        c. because of events <strong>beyond</strong> the control;<br />
                        d. then k is void;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under contract law a material condition of every contract is that&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">performance of contract duties must be objectively possible</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to perform. The inability of a contract party to perform is irrelevant, as long as performance, in general, is possible. But</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;if performance becomes impossible&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">because of&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">events beyond the control&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">of the parties the contract becomes void.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Impracticability</strong></p>
                    <p>a. performance by a party<br />
                        b. would be so financially burdensome;<br />
                        c. because of events beyond our control;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">A Court (a judge, in equity) has the authority to declare a contract void if&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">performance by a party</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">would be so&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">financially burdensome</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, because of&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">events beyond the control&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">of the parties, that it would&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">cause an injustice</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Frustration of Purpose </strong></p>
                    <p>a. failure of condition;<br />
                        b. beyond their control;<br />
                        c. will deny one of the parties, the benefit of bargain;<br />
                        d. condition is implied material condition;<br />
                        e. failure of which excuses both parties from agreement.                    </p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under contract law, if the parties enter into a contract knowing that the<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;failure of some condition</strong>beyond&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">their control&nbsp;</strong>will&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">deny one of the parties</strong>&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">benefit</strong>&nbsp;of the bargain, that&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">condition is an implied material condition&nbsp;</strong>of the contract, the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">failure of which excuses both parties</strong>&nbsp;from the agreement . When the purpose of the contract is frustrated, the performance of the contract may be excused.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Mutual Mistake</strong></p>
                    <p>a. misunderstanding of material fact by both parties;<br />
                        b. there is no meeting of minds;<br />
                        c. contract is void from beginning;</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under PEERLESS when both parties enter into a contract because of a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">misunderstanding as to a material fact</strong>, there is&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">no &quot;meeting of the minds&quot;</strong>&nbsp;and the contract is&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">void</strong>&nbsp;from the beginning.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">A mutual mistake can void the contract if both parties are<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;honestly mistaken about a material fact</strong>&nbsp;of the contract.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp;                     </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Unitlateral Mistake </strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Majority View:</strong><br />
                        a. misunderstanding of material fact by one party;<br />
                        b. legally bound to K<br />
                        c. unless other party knew of the mistake;<br />
                        d. contract is voidable by mistaken party</p>
                    <p><strong>Minority View:</strong><br />
                        a. k is legally voidable if<br />
                        b. mistaken party discover mistake quickly before other party relies on it;<br />
                        c. give prompt notice;<br />
                        d. reimburse the party;</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under contract law, when one party enters into a contract because of a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">misunderstanding as to a material fact</strong>&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">majority view</strong>&nbsp;is that the parties are&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">legally bound</strong>&nbsp;to the contract unless&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">the other party knew</strong>&nbsp;or should have known&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">of the mistake</strong>, and in that case the contract is voidable by the mistaken party.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under a minority view the contract is legally voidable by the mistaken party in any event if they 1)&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">discover the mistake quickly</strong>&nbsp;before the other party substantially relies on the contract, 2)&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">give prompt notice</strong>&nbsp;of the mistake, and 3)&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">reimburse the other party</strong>&nbsp;for any expenses caused by the mistake.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>D. THIRD PARTY CONTRACTS </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Third Party Beneficiary </strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Third Party Beneficiary</strong><br />
                        a. legally enforced contract<br />
                        b. entered by 2 parties<br />
                        c. intending purpose<br />
                        d. for benefitting third party</p>
                    <p><strong>Incidental Beneficiary</strong><br />
                        a. one who is not intended to benefit<br />
                        b. from contract between others<br />
                        c. has no ability to enforce the contract or seek damages</p>
                    <p><strong>Creditor Beneficiaries</strong><br />
                        a. promisee enters into the third party beneficiary contract<br />
                        b. to satisfy legal obligations<br />
                        c. intended third party beneficiaries have legal right to enforce the contract against promisee<br />
                    d. intended third party beneficiary is called creditor beneficiary</p>
                    <p><strong>Donee Beneficiaries</strong><br />
                        a. promisee enters into the third party beneficiary contract<br />
                        b. for gratitutious purpose<br />
                        c. Intended third party beneficiary has not legal right to enforce the contract against the promisee<br />
                        d. Intended third party beneficiary is called donee beneficiary</p>
                    <p><strong>Rights of Third Party Beneficiary </strong></p>
                    <p>Intended third party beneficiary always have <strong>standing</strong> to <strong>enforce</strong> the contract against the <strong>promisors</strong> whether they are donee or creditor.</p>
                    <p><strong>Defenses</strong></p>
                    <p>Promisors can raise defense against intended third party beneficiary.</p>
                    <p>Promisee can raise defense against intended third party beneficiary.</p>
                    <p><strong>Standing </strong></p>
                    <p>Parties seeking a remedy must have a legal right to enforce the contract. this is called standing.</p>
                    <p>Promisor and promise have standing based on original contract.</p>
                    <p>Intended third party beneficiary has standing when their righs are vested.</p>
                    <p><strong>Vesting</strong></p>
                    <p>Third party beneficiary can enforce the contract if their rights have vested. Vesting means they act in reliance of the contract.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;  </p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Assignments</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Definition:</strong><br />
                        An assignment is a transfer of contractual rights to the third party. </p>
                    <p>An assigment which declars &quot;all my rights&quot; is nothing but assignment and delegation.</p>
                    <p><strong>Parties</strong></p>
                    <p>Parties promised benefits of a contracts are promisees of the contract. Promisees can convey their contract rights to third parties.</p>
                    <p>Promisee become Assignor and third party will become Assignee.</p>
                    <p>So we have Promisee/Assignor and Assignee.</p>
                    <p>and we have promisor (obligor) from original master contract.</p>
                    <p>Law favors assignments. Here concern is who gets paid.</p>
                    <p><strong>Covenant &quot;Not to Assign&quot;</strong></p>
                    <p>Promises to &quot;not assign&quot; contract rights are considered <strong>covenants</strong> unles contract language makes it quite clear that non-assignments is intended to be an express condition with wordings like &quot;<strong>All assigments are null and void</strong>&quot;</p>
                    <p>Anti assignments clause only destroys the right to assign, but not the power. To destory the power, we need above statement.</p>
                    <p>Contract cannot be assigned if duty of promisor is changed substantially.</p>
                    <p><strong>Breach of covenant &quot;not to assign&quot;</strong></p>
                    <p>When &quot;covenant not to assign&quot; right is breached, it is a minor breach of contract by promisee/assignor, but burden is on non breaching party to prove the damages. </p>
                    <p><strong>Effective</strong></p>
                    <p>Assignments become effective when it is clearly communicated to promisors.</p>
                    <p>Clear expressed statement by promisee to convey the rights to idendified assignees.</p>
                    <p>Statement like &quot;I hereby give you...&quot;</p>
                    <p>Promisors are <strong>obligated to convey contract benefits to the assignees</strong> upon receiving the notice of contract assignments.</p>
                    <p>Promisee <strong>lose their rights to receive contract benefits</strong> upon receipt of notice by assignees that do not reject them.</p>
                    <p><strong>Promisee loses standing</strong></p>
                    <p>After effective assignment, promisee loses the contract rights and so they cannot do not have standing to enforce the contract.</p>
                    <p>Gratitutous Assignees and Contractual Assignees.</p>
                    <p>Promisee are not liable to gratitutous assignees but liable to contractual assignees.</p>
                    <p>Promisee is liable to promisors.</p>
                    <p>Promisors are liable to all assignees.</p>
                    <p><strong>Defenses</strong></p>
                    <p>promisee can raise defense against the promisors and assignees.,</p>
                    <p>2 contracts master with promisor and promisee and assignment contract with promisee and assignee. </p>
                    <p><strong>Payment to promisee after assignment</strong></p>
                    <p>if promisor pays to promisee after assignment, he is still liable to assignee.   </p>
                    <p>&nbsp;   </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Delegation</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Definition:</strong><br />
                    A delegation is<strong> transfer of contractual duty</strong> to a third party.</p>
                    <p>There are promisor and promisee in a contract.</p>
                    <p>When promisor arrange for third parties to perform the contract duties, it is called delegation.</p>
                    <p>Promisors are callled delegators and third party who will perform the duty are called delegatee. Promisee remain as it is.</p>
                    <p>Promisee is third party beneficiary in case of delegation as the benefit from promisor and third party is to promisee.</p>
                    <p><strong>Non Delegable Duties</strong></p>
                    <p>Duties cannot be delegated if they are</p>
                    <p>i. too personal</p>
                    <p>ii. contract prohits them</p>
                    <p>iii. materially change the benefits which promisee will receive.</p>
                    <p><strong>Promisor Liability</strong></p>
                    <p>A promisor cannot escape liability for master contract by just delegating the duty.</p>
                    <p><strong>Effective</strong></p>
                    <p>i. promisor manifest its clear intent to delegate the duty.</p>
                    <p>ii. duty to perform exists</p>
                    <p>iii. delegatee agrees to assume the duties of the promisor    </p>
                    <p>Contractual Delegatee</p>
                    <p>Is liable to Delegator and Promisee</p>
                    <p>Gratituous Delegatee </p>
                    <p>Is not liable to Promisee or delegator</p>
                    <p>Promisees are not liable to delegatees , they are only liable to delegator</p>
                    <p>Promisors are liable to contractual delegatee</p>
                    <p>Defenses</p>
                    <p>Defenses of promisors and promisees are unchanged.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;    </p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>E. BREACH </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Anticipatory Breach</strong></p>
                    <p>a. clear statement that party will not perform;<br />
                        b. future duties when they become due;<br />
                        c. its a major breach;<br />
                        d. non-breaching party is excused from performance;<br />
                        e. future duties of breaching party is accelerated to present;</p>
                    <p><strong>Reasonable Belief:</strong></p>
                    <p>a. reassonable belief that party will not perform;<br />
                        b. so they can ask reasonable assurance like the financial gurantee;<br />
                        c. and if they are demanded but not provided then it is an anticipatory breach;                         </p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under contract law an anticipatory breach (or anticipatory repudiation) is a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">CLEAR STATEMENT OR INDICATION</strong>&nbsp;that a party&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">WILL NOT PERFORM</strong>&nbsp;future contractual duties when they become due. This is a major breach as to those duties, the non-breaching party is&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">EXCUSED</strong>&nbsp;from performance of all remaining contractual duties, and the future duties of the breaching party are&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">ACCELERATED</strong>&nbsp;to the present.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">If a party has a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">REASONABLE BASIS</strong>&nbsp;to believe the other party may not perform future contractual duties, the party may demand&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">REASONABLE ASSURANCES</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">REFUSE TO PERFORM&nbsp;</strong>until they are provided. Reasonable assurances generally means a financial guarantee or payment into escrow.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">If reasonable assurances are properly demanded and not provided, the failure to respond constitutes an anticipatory breach.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Breach: Major/Minor </strong></p>
                    <p>First party who breached is the breaching party.</p>
                    <p><strong>Definition:</strong><br />
                    a. failure to perform contractual duties</p>
                    <p><strong>For Common Law</strong><br />
                        a. major breach is one which deprives the benefit of the bargain;<br />
                        b. or violation of express or implied material condition;<br />
                        c. major breach excuses the non breaching party from all further performances;<br />
                        d. accelerates the duty of breaching party to present;<br />
                        e. so that non breaching party can seek immediate payment of damages;</p>
                    <p><strong>For UCC (Perfect Tender Rule)</strong><br />
                        a. any shipment of non-confirming goods is a breach;</p>
                    <p><strong>For UCC (Divisible Contracts)</strong><br />
                        a. breach with respect to any shipment does not constitute breach of entire contract.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Realize the<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;first party to breach</strong>&nbsp;a contract<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;is the breaching party</strong>&nbsp;and after that the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">other party is the non-breaching party</strong>&nbsp;no matter what they do later.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">For&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">COMMON LAW</strong>&nbsp;say,</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under contract law a BREACH is a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">failure to perform a contractual duty</strong>&nbsp;when it becomes due. A MAJOR BREACH is either an act which&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">deprives</strong>&nbsp;the other party of the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">BENEFIT OF THE BARGAIN</strong>or the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">violation of an EXPRESS OR IMPLIED MATERIAL CONDITION</strong>&nbsp;by a party, regardless of its effect on the other party. A major breach&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">EXCUSES&nbsp;</strong>the non-breaching party from&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">all further performance&nbsp;</strong>of contractual duties and&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">ACCELERATES</strong>&nbsp;the future contractual duties of the breaching party&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">to the present&nbsp;</strong>so the non-breaching party can seek<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;IMMEDIATE PAYMENT OF DAMAGES</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">For&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">UCC</strong>&nbsp;say,</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">PERFECT TENDER RULE</strong>&nbsp;of the UCC&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">any shipment of non-conforming goods</strong>&nbsp;is a breach of contract. There is no distinction between major and minor breaches.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">For&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">UCC DIVISIBLE CONTRACT SITUATION</strong>&nbsp;say,</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the UCC a breach with respect to<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;any shipment of goods under a DIVISIBLE CONTRACT does not constitute a breach of the entire contract.</strong>&nbsp;A DIVISIBLE contract is one under which goods are to be delivered in separate shipments which can each be evaluated separately under the contract.</p>                    <p>&nbsp;                                          </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Waiver of Breach </strong></p>
                    <p>a. non breaching party lets the breaching party;<br />
                        b. continue the performance after the major breach;<br />
                        c. it waives the breach and waiver cannot be retracted;<br />
                        d. and it becomes minor breach;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under contract law if a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">non-breaching party lets the breaching party continue performance</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">after a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">major breach</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;it&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">WAIVES THE BREACH</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">. The waiver cannot be revoked, and the non-breaching party is forever ESTOPPED from citing the breach as major and can only cite it as a minor breach.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Breach of Implied Covenent (Good Faith) </strong></p>
                    <p>a. parties must act in good faith;<br />
                        b. help other parties to enjoy the benefits of the contract;<br />
                        c. they will not act in a way to prevent this from occuring.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">An&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">IMPLIED MATERIAL CONDITION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;of every contract is that the parties must act in&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">good faith</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">and are bound by an&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">IMPLIED COVENANT</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;that they will act as reasonably necessary</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;to help the other parties</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;enjoy the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">benefits of the contract&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">and that they will not act in any way to prevent that from occurring.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Waiver of Condition </strong></p>
                    <p>a. contractual duty that is subject to condition precedent;<br />
                        b. condition fails to hold;<br />
                        c. party waives the condition;<br />
                        d. party can retract the waiver;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under contract law if a party performs a contractual&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">duty</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;that is subject to a</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;condition precedent</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">at a time the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">condition fails to hold</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, the party&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">WAIVES THE CONDITION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">. But after a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">condition has been waived&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">the waiving party has a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">legal right to retract the waiver</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">. Nevertheless, a Court of EQUITY may estop the retraction based on considerations of equitable estoppel.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Accord &amp; Satisfaction </strong></p>
                    <p>a. agreement by the parties;<br />
                        b. to settle a reasonable claim;<br />
                        c. by one party;<br />
                        d. that other party has breached the original contract;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under contract law an&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">ACCORD AND SATISFACTION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;is binding on&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">both parties</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;if there is an agreement by the parties to&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">settle a reasonable</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;and good faith&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">claim</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;by&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">one party</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;that the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">other party has breached the original contract</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>F. REMEDIES </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Common law remedy for Non Breaching &amp; Breaching Party </strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Compensatory Damage</strong></p>
                    <p>a. sum of reliance damage, expectation damage, incidental damage, consequential damage.</p>
                    <p><strong>Reliance Damage</strong></p>
                    <p>a. Out of pocket expense<br />
                        b. before the breach<br />
                        c. in reliance on the contract</p>
                    <p><strong>Expectation Damage</strong></p>
                    <p>a. expected benefits<br />
                        b. lost due to breach</p>
                    <p><strong>Incidental Damage</strong></p>
                    <p>a. out of pocket expense<br />
                        b. lost because of the breach<br />
                        c. after the breach</p>
                    <p><strong>Consequential Damage </strong>(CCCC)</p>
                    <p>a. Lost profits on collateral contracts<br />
                        b. that failed because of the breach</p>
                    <p>Under Hadley &amp; Baxendle, Consequential damage can only be awarded in foreseeable situation, where</p>
                    <p>CCCC</p>
                    <p>C - contemplated, foreseeable<br />
                        C - certain in amount<br />
                        C - cause is breach<br />
                        C - could not be avoided</p>
                    <p><strong>Remedy for the Breaching Party</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Substantial performance</strong></p>
                    <p>a. Non breaching party is obligated for the offset price over the contract price for damages caused</p>
                    <p><strong>Major Breach</strong></p>
                    <p>a. Non breaching party is free from the obligation and can recover all damages                        </p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under common law the non-breaching party has a right to&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">COMPENSATORY DAMAGES</strong>&nbsp;calculated as the sum of 1) RELIANCE DAMAGES,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">out-of-pocket expenses</strong>&nbsp;the non-breaching party paid before the breach&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">in reliance on the contract</strong>, 2) EXPECTATION DAMAGES, the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">expected benefits</strong>of the contract lost because of the breach, 3) INCIDENTAL DAMAGES,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">out- of-pocket expenses</strong>&nbsp;the non-breaching party paid&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">because of the breach</strong>&nbsp;(e.g. storage costs) and 4) CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES, lost profits on collateral contracts that failed because of the breach.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">Hadley v. Baxendale</strong>&nbsp;CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES can only be awarded if, at the time the original contract was executed, the breaching party&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">knew</strong>&nbsp;of or otherwise could have contemplated the non-breaching party would&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">enter into collateral contracts</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">would lose profits</strong>&nbsp;on them as a result of a contract breach.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The burden is on a non-breaching party to prove the damages suffered with&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">CERTAINTY</strong>, to prove they were&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">CAUSED</strong>&nbsp;BY THE BREACH, and that they&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">COULD NOT BE AVOIDED&nbsp;</strong>after the breach occurred. By implication this gives the non-breaching party a duty to mitigate damages.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">If the breaching party has&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">SUBSTANTIALLY PERFORMED</strong>, the non-breaching party is still obligated under the contract with an&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">OFFSET</strong>&nbsp;for damages against the contract price. But if the breaching party is in&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">MAJOR BREACH</strong>&nbsp;the non-breaching party is freed from all obligations under the contract and has a right to an award of all damages caused.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>UCC Remedies of Non Breaching Buyer </strong></p>
                    <p>Non breaching buyer can: </p>
                    <p>a. <strong>accept</strong> or <strong>reject</strong> non conforming goods.<br />
                        b. or <strong>repudiate</strong> the contract and <strong>cover it</strong><br />
                        c. or <strong>affirm the contract</strong> and <strong>ask for </strong>conforming goods;</p>
                    <p><strong>Measure of damage</strong></p>
                    <p>a. is the excess if any, of cover or market price over the contract price</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">PERFECT TENDER RULE</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;of the UCC a non-breaching buyer can either&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">ACCEPT</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;or&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">REJECT</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;non-conforming goods. Also they can&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">REPUDIATE</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;the contract and COVER, or they can&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">AFFIRM</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;the contract and&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">DEMAND CONFORMING GOODS</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">. The measure of damages is the excess, if any, of&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">market or cover price</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;over the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">contract price</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>UCC Remedies of Non Breaching Seller </strong></p>
                    <p>Sellers normally <strong>do not get lost profits</strong> in UCC.</p>
                    <p>Under<strong> lost volume situation</strong>, they <strong>get</strong> the <strong>profit</strong>. Here seller has unlimited supply of goods and buyer breached the contract. Here Seller recovers the profit if buyer breached as he would have sold it to someone else. </p>
                    <p>Non breaching seller can </p>
                    <p>a. <strong>sell rejected</strong> and conforming goods <br />
                    b. at public or private <strong>salvage</strong><br />
                        c. with <strong>notice</strong> to the buyer<br />
                        d. demand excess of <strong>contract price over salvage</strong> price.</p>
                    <p><strong>Special made goods</strong></p>
                    <p>a. here seller cannot sell the goods to anyone else<br />
                        b. so he can get full value of contract price.                         </p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the UCC a non-breaching seller can sell rejected but conforming goods at a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">PUBLIC</strong>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">PRIVATE SALVAGE SALE</strong>&nbsp;(with NOTICE TO BREACHING BUYER) and demand the excess, if any, of the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">CONTRACT PRICE</strong>&nbsp;over the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">SALVAGE SALE</strong>&nbsp;price.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Alternatively, in a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">LOST-VOLUME SITUATION</strong>&nbsp;where sellers cannot effectively sell the same goods to someone else, they can demand the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">BENEFIT OF THE BARGAIN</strong>&nbsp;of their &quot;lost profits&quot; - the excess, if any, of the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">CONTRACT PRICE</strong>&nbsp;over their cost of acquiring the goods.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">And if the goods have been&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">special made</strong>&nbsp;or for some other reason&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">can not be sold elsewhere</strong>&nbsp;the non-breaching seller can &quot;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">sue on the contract price</strong>&quot; to get a judgment for that amount.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>UCC Remedies of Breaching Seller </strong></p>
                    <p>Breaching seller who</p>
                    <p>a. give notice of an intent to cure;<br />
                        b. can cure the breach within the contracted period<br />
                        c. also gets extra reasonable time<br />
                        d. if non confirming goods have been shipped with 
                    reasonable belief that it would satisfy the buyer. </p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under the UCC a breaching seller that&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">GIVES NOTIC</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">E of an intent to cure has an absolute right to cure the breach&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">WITHIN THE CONTRACT PERIOD</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, and also has a right to&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">REASONABLE EXTRA TIME</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;in which to cure beyond the contract period if&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">non-conforming goods</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;have been shipped with a</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;reasonable belief</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;they would satisfy the needs of the buyer.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Liquidated Damages </strong></p>
                    <p>a. sole remedy of the non-breaching party is the specified amount of the money damages</p>
                    <p>if </p>
                    <p>a. damages arising from the breach is UNCERTAIN at time of contract;<br />
                        b. specified amount is reasonable;<br />
                        c. reasonable remedy for non breaching party</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">LIQUIDATED DAMAGES CLAUSES specify that the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">sole remedy</strong>&nbsp;of the non-breaching party is a<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">specified amount</strong>&nbsp;of money damages.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">These clauses are only enforceable if 1)&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">DAMAGES</strong>&nbsp;arising from a breach were&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">UNCERTAIN</strong>&nbsp;at the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">TIME OF CONTRACT</strong>, 2) the specified amount was&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">REASONABLE</strong>&nbsp;at the time of contract, and 3) enforcement after a breach will provide a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">REASONABLE REMEDY</strong>&nbsp;for the non-breaching party.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Saving Doctrine for Unilateral Contracts </strong></p>
                    <p>a. prohibit the offeror;<br />
                        b. from revoking a unilateral contract;<br />
                        c. for a reasonable period of time;<br />
                        d. after becoming aware that offeree has begun performance;</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">In case of Unilateral Contracts</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the common law an offeror&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">could revoke her offer at any time</strong>&nbsp;before acceptance. Modernly&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">SAVING DOCTRINES</strong>&nbsp;have been adopted to prohibit the offeror of a unilateral contract from&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">revoking</strong>&nbsp;for a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">reasonable time</strong>&nbsp;after becoming&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">aware</strong>&nbsp;that the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">offeree has begun performance</strong>in acceptance.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Implied in Law (Quisa Contract) </strong></p>
                    <p>a. court may award amount;<br />
                        b. necessary to prevent unjust enrichment;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">The Court may either award the amount necessary to prevent an unjust enrichment to the respondent.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Promissor Estoppel / Detrimental Reliance </strong></p>
                    <p>Unenforceable at court of law because of lack of consideration<br />
                        can be enforced at court of equity to avoid injustice<br />
                        party must have clean hands</p>
                    <p>a. party to be bound made a promise;<br />
                        b. with intent to induce reliance;<br />
                        c. and there was a reasonable reliance;<br />
                        d. failure to enforce the promise - would cause an injustice;</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the theory of PROMISSORY ESTOPPEL an&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">agreement</strong>&nbsp;that otherwise is&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">unenforceable at law</strong>for&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">lack of consideration</strong>&nbsp;may be&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">enforced at equity</strong>&nbsp;to the extent necessary to&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">avoid injustice</strong>. In order to plead equity a party must have&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">CLEAN HANDS</strong>. Promissory Estoppel applies where the party to be bound made a 1)&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">promise</strong>&nbsp;with 2) intent to<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;induce reliance</strong>&nbsp;and there 3) was&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">reasonable reliance</strong>&nbsp;and 4)&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">failure to enforce the promise</strong>&nbsp;would cause an injustice.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the theory of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">DETRIMENTAL RELIANCE</strong>&nbsp;an agreement that otherwise is unenforceable at law for deliberately&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">false representations of fact</strong>&nbsp;by the respondent OR deliberately&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">misleading behavior</strong>&nbsp;of the respondent may be enforced at equity to the extent necessary to<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;avoid injustice</strong>. In order to plead equity a party must have&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">CLEAN HANDS</strong>. Detrimental Reliance applies where the party to be bound made a 1)&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">promise</strong>&nbsp;with 2) intent to<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;induce reliance</strong>&nbsp;and there 3) was&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">reasonable reliance</strong>&nbsp;and 4)<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;failure to enforce the promise</strong>&nbsp;would cause an injustice.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" /></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Equitable Restitution </strong></p>
                    <p>a. awarded by court of equity<br />
                        b. when parties have no legal remedy<br />
                        c. purpose to compensate injuries<br />
                    </p>
                    <p>a. to prevent unjust enrichment<br />
                        b. prevent frustration of reasonable expectations<br />
                        c. restore status quo</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">EQUITABLE RESTITUTION is a remedy awarded by a Court of EQUITY when the parties have&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">no adequate legal remedy</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">. The purpose may be to compensate for&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">injuries suffered</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">,&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">prevent unjust enrichment</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, prevent&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">frustration of reasonable expectations</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, or restore the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">status quo</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;                     </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Specific Performance </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Court directing the parties <br />
                        b. 
                    to deliver the possesion of unique property. </p>
                    <p>Cannot be done on labor.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
        </table></td>
        <td width="40%" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>A. INTENTIONAL TORTS </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">1. Intentional </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>2. Assault </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Volitional Act<br />
                        b. Requisite Intent<br />
                        c. Causation<br />
                        d. Immediate apprehension of harmful or offensive touching</p>
                    <p>a. <strong>Volitional Act</strong> is one where D performs voluntarily <br />
                            <br />
                            e.g. It can be inferred from the fact that since D was acting of his own accord, as opposed to accidentally or mistakenly when he 
did ...... at Plaintiff. There is no evidence in the fact pattern that D accidentally<br />
did this ..... and it was not an involuntary action. Therefore, this requirement is met.<br />
<br />
b.<strong> Intent:</strong> D must intend to cause apprehension or must be substantially certain that such conduct would occur.<br />
<br />
e.g. It can be reasonably 
inferred from D's act of ...... at P that he actually intended to make 
contact with P and at least cause P apprehension of being hit by the .....</p>
                    <p>If actual intent is not proven, in the alternative, the <strong>substantial certainty</strong> element would be met. A reasonable person would be substantially certain that if one violently ........ at another that person will be apprehensive and attempt to move out of the way to avoid a harmful touching by the shopping cart. Therefore, D knew to a substantial certainty that he would cause P to be in apprehension. Thus, the intent element is met.<br />
                        <br />
                            <strong>c. Causation: </strong>Whether P caused the D to be in apprehension of harmful or offensive touching.<br />
                            <strong>d. Apprehension:</strong> P must actually be apprehensive of a harmful or offensive touching.</p>
                    <p>D intent to cause apprehension and it does cause the apprehension. </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>3. Battery </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Volitional Act<br />
                        b. Intent<br />
                        c. Causation<br />
                        d. Harmful or Offensive Touching</p>
                    <p>a. <strong>Volitional Act</strong> is one where D performs voluntarily <br />
b.<strong> Intent:</strong> D must intend to inflict harmful or offensive touching or must be substantially certain such contact will occur.<br />
c. <strong>Causation:</strong> Battery requires actual contact with the person or closely connected to the person and done by the act of the Defendant. <br />
<strong>d. Harmful or Offensive Touching: </strong>Contact must be harmful or offensive. </p>
                    <p>Plaintiff must prove<br />
                    a. Defendant <strong>intent</strong> to commit a harmful or offensive touching;<br />
                        b. <strong>actual touching</strong> which cause harm or offensive;<br />
                        c. the absence of consent.                    </p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">4. False ImprisLonment </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">5. IIED </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">6. Trespass to Land </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">7. Trespass to Chattel </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">8. Transferred Intent </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>B. TORT DEFENSES </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"> Damages in Torts </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">Self Defense </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Necessity </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Reasonable Force<br />
                        b. as Necessary<br />
                        c. to protect self, others, and property</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under tort law a person is privileged to act reasonably as&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">NECESSARY</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to protect their&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">own safety</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">safety of others</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, and the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">safety of property</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Reasonable acts done to protect the<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;property of others</strong>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">PUBLIC NECESSITY</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">absolutely privileged</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Reasonable acts done to protect the defendant's&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">own property</strong>&nbsp;are a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">PRIVATE NECESSITY</strong>&nbsp;and only a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">qualified privilege</strong>.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Recapture </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Reasonable Force<br />
                        b. They have asked for and refused to give chattel <br />
                        c. Fresh pursuit<br />
                        d. lost possession with no fault of their own.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under tort law a person has a qualified privilege to use&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">reasonable</strong>&nbsp;force to&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">RECAPTURE</strong>&nbsp;their own chattel if</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">1) they have&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">asked</strong>&nbsp;for and have been&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">refused</strong>&nbsp;return of the chattel, and</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">2) they are in<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;fresh pursuit</strong>&nbsp;of wrongfully taken chattel, or</p>
