            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>C. NEGLIGENCE </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p>Negligence</p>
                    <p>What is Bob's liability in Negligence?</p>
                    <p><strong>A. Negligence</strong></p>
                    <p>Plantiff seeking to establish liability in negligence must show that the defendant <strong>owed a legal duty</strong> to the plaintiff, that<strong> he breached </strong>that duty, that the breach of that duty was the <strong>actual and proximate cause</strong> of injury to the plaintiff, and that the plaintiff <strong>suffered damages</strong> as a result of defendant's conduct. </p>
                    <p><strong>B. Duty</strong></p>
                    <p>The general rule of duty is there is no duty unless there is an affirmative act or special relationship. </p>
                    <p>Under the <strong>Cardoza view</strong> the defendant owess a duty to only foreseeable plaintiff's. The <strong>minority view</strong> was seen in <strong>Andrews</strong> where everyone <strong>owes a duty</strong> to the <strong>world</strong> at large. </p>
                    <p><strong>Duty to care for the P</strong></p>
                    <p>D has a duty to take affirmative action to benefit the P where there exists a special relationship between the D and P from which the D derives <strong>economic benefits</strong>.  (Employee / Employer, Student / Teacher). </p>
                    <p><strong>Duty to control</strong></p>
                    <p>D has a duty to take affirmative action to protect P where the D has a special relationship with a third person that gives the D power to control the behavior.  </p>
                    <p>D (as employer) has a duty to the P to exercise reasonable care in hiring employees. </p>
                    <p><strong>Duty to warn</strong></p>
                    <p>In some jurisdictions a D who has the requisite special relationship with a 3rd person who becomes aware that the 3rd person intendes to do specific harm has a duty to warn the P of the harm.  </p>
                    <p><strong>Standard of Care</strong> is what a reasonable person will do in the same situation. </p>
                    <p><strong>C. Breach</strong></p>
                    <p>The defendant breaches the duty to the plaintiff if he fails to conduct himself as a reasonable prudent person in same or similar circumstances. </p>
                    <p><strong>Negligence Per Se - Statute</strong></p>
                    <p>i. Injury caused by D's conduct is the type which the statute was intended to prevent.</p>
                    <p>ii. P was a member of class to be proteced.</p>
                    <p>iii. D's violation is not excused.   </p>
                    <p><strong>Common Carriers (Innkeepers, Utility co)</strong> - Common carriers traditionally have a duty to avoid harm through the exercise fo the highest degree of care and precaution.</p>
                    <p><strong>Doctors (Lawyers, Architects, Professional Level, Practitioner):</strong> The reasonable person possessed the customary level of <strong>specialized knowledge </strong>and expertise of a practictioner in good standing of the same or similar trad as the D.</p>
                    <p><strong>P's not on the land:</strong> Duty of reasonable care to prevent injury.</p>
                    <p><strong>Trespassers: </strong>Defendant has no duty to warn for unknown trespassers.</p>
                    <p><strong>Frequent/Known Trespassers:</strong> If D knows or reasonably should have known of frequent trespassers then there is duty to warn of hidden dangers of which the D knows and is aware. </p>
                    <p><strong>Child Trespassers: </strong>Duty to exercise reasonable care and possibly to warn of known dangers.  </p>
                    <p><strong>Licensee:</strong> A person who enters onto the D's land with the D's permission who does not enter for the purpose benefiting the Defendant or defendants activities. D has a duty to exercise reasonable care to protect from injury arising from the activities conduct by the D or on the D's behalf.</p>
                    <p><strong>Invitee: </strong>Business invitee / Public Invitee - Duty to exercise reasonable care to prevent injury to invitees caused by activities conducted on the D's land. D has a duty to exercise reasonable care to discover dangerous artificial conditions which the invitee would not be aware, to warn of the existence of such dangers, if warning not sufficient then to provide precautions.</p>
                    <p><strong>Landlord Tenent's:</strong> Landlord duty to upkeep common areas.  </p>
                    <p>Res Ipsa - No Idea &quot;falling cow&quot;</p>
                    <p>Failure to act as a reasonable prudent person</p>
                    <p><strong>Learned Hand Discussion</strong> - Social Utility; extent of injury; burden, probability</p>
                    <p>If the burden of taking precautions is less than the probablity of injury times the severity plus social utility, then the D breached his duty by not taking those precautions. </p>
                    <p><strong>D. Causation</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Actual Cause</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>But For:</strong> Defendants conduct was the cause in fact of an event if that event would not have occured <strong>but for</strong> the D's conduct. </p>
                    <p><strong>Substantial Factor:</strong> A defendant's conduct is the cause | act of the P's injury if the conduct was a <strong>substiantial factor</strong> in bringing about the injury. </p>
                    <p><strong>Proximate Cause </strong></p>
                    <p>If a reasonable person would have anticipated the extent and type of injury by the D's risk creating conduct, the P's injury was foreseeable. Foreseeability Test. </p>
                    <p><strong>Eggshell Plaintiff: </strong>A reasonable person would have foreseen the D's conduct causing the type of injury but not the extent, then the D's conduct is still the legal cause - Eggshell plaintiff. </p>
                    <p><strong>Polemis: </strong>The nature of the unforeseeable injury is immaterial.</p>
                    <p><strong>Wagon Mound:</strong> Only if teh type of injury is one that could have reasonably foreseen.</p>
                    <p><strong>Intervening:</strong> A force combined with the D's conduct is intervening if it arises AFTER the D's conduct has begun.   </p>
                    <p><strong>Dependent: </strong>Foreseeable, normal. Rescues, negligent medical treatment, suicide, etc. </p>
                    <p><strong>Independent:</strong> Reasonably foreseeable, Negligence of a third party, Illness, accident, etc. </p>
                    <p><strong>E. Damages      </strong></p>
                    <p>General Damages</p>
                    <p>Special Damages</p>
                    <p><strong>F. Defenses</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Contributory Negligence</strong></p>
                    <p>Under common law the P was required to exercise due care to protect himself from injury by the D and any contributory negligence on the part of P was a complete bar of recovery. </p>
                    <p><strong>Comparative Negligence  </strong></p>
                    <p>Comparative negligence is now the modern rule where the P's negligence contributes to his own injury total damages are apportioned upon a determination of the fault of each party.</p>
                    <p>Pure: 99%, 1%</p>
                    <p>Partial Comparative Negligence: 51%  </p>
                    <p>Assumption of Risks </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p>a. Failure to exercise degree of care<br />
                    b. that a reasonable prudent person would do in same or similar situation</p>
                    <p>P has to prove duty, breach, causation and damages to prevail.</p>
                    <p>D owed a duty, he breached that duty and that was the cause of the injury and P suffered the injury.   </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Negligence</strong></p>
                    <p>a. Failure to exercise;<br />
                        b. that degree of care;<br />
                        c. that a reasonable prudent person would do;<br />
                    d. in same or similar situation;</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Duty</strong></p>
                    <p>No duty to act to defend others. Duty arises in five situations:</p>
                    <p><strong>SCRAP</strong></p>
                    <p>Statute, Contract, Relationship, Assumption, Peril.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;  </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Duty Based on Peril </strong></p>
                    <p>a. D who creates foreseeable dangers to others<br />
                        b. have duty to act reasonably <br />
                        c. to protect others from those dangers</p>
                    <p><strong>CARDOZA VIEW</strong><br />
                        a. D who creates peril do not have duty outside the zone of danger.<br />
                        b. Zone of danger is the area where D's act causes peril.</p>
                    <p><strong>ANDREWS VIEW</strong><br />
                        a. D who creates peril is liable to anyone actually and proximally got injured, even if outside the zone of danger.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;                     </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Duty Based on Premises Liability </strong></p>
                    <p>Duty is based on relationship. Occupier of the land has a duty to those who come on the land and off the land.</p>
                    <p>a. No Duty to unknown trespassers<br />
                        b. <strong>Warn</strong> and <strong>protect</strong> the <strong>licensees / known trespassers</strong> from the known hidden dangers and artificial conditions.<br />
                        c.<strong> Inspect, warn and protect</strong> the <strong>invitees</strong> from the known hidden dangers and artificial conditions.<br />
                    d. Occupier has duty to conduct and control activities with due care to prevent injury to people off the land. </p>
                    <p>Invitees are peole who come for the benefit of the occupier.</p>
                    <p>Licensees are the people who do not come for the benefit of the occupier. </p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Duty Based on Negligence Per Se </strong></p>
                    <p>a. <strong>Statute</strong> created <strong>duty</strong><br />
                    b. <strong>Violation</strong> of statute is <strong>breach</strong><br />
                        Purpose of statute is<br />
                        c
                        . to <strong>protect the class of people</strong> to which the plaintiff belongs<br />
                        d. from the <strong>injury</strong> which plaintiff suffered.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Assuming the criminal statute is silent on civil liability, a plaintiff must meet a five-part test in order to be able to use violation of the criminal statute as proof of negligence:</span><br style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" />
                        <br style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" />
                        <span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">1. A&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">criminal statute</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, ordinance, or administrative regulation imposes a specific duty upon someone for the protection of others (for example, a statute imposes a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">30 mph speed limit</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">).</span><br style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" />
                        <span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">2. The&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">defendant neglects</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to perform that duty (for example,&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">the defendant speeds</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">).</span><br style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" />
                        <span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">3. Plaintiff is within the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">class of people&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">whom the statute was designed to protect (for example,</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;the speeding statute is designed to protect pedestrians</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;and other drivers).</span><br style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" />
                        <span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">4. The statute was designed to protect against the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">type of accident</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;the defendant causes (for example, the speeding statute is designed to&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">protect against collisions</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;between cars and other cars, people, or property).</span><br style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;" />
                    <span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">5. Plaintiff's injuries were caused by&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">defendant's violation</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;of the statute, ordinance, or regulation (for example,&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">the pedestrian would not have been injured had the driver not been speeding</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">).</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Attractive Nuisance Doctrine </strong></p>
                    <p>a. <strong>Children likely to trespass:</strong><br />
                        Possessor knows or has reason to know that children are likely to trespass in the location of the danger.<br />
                        b.<strong> Condition involve risk of harm</strong><br />
                        the possessor knows or has reason to know that the condition will involve an unreasonable risk of death or serious bodily harm to such children;<br />
                        c. <strong>Children could not discover condition because of age </strong><br />
                        the children, because of their youth, do not discover the  condition or realise the risk involved;<br />
                        d. <strong>Burden of elimination is less</strong><br />
                        the utility to the possessor of maintaining the condition and the burden of eliminating the danger are slight as compared with the risk to the children involved;<br />
                    e. <strong>Breach by failing to take care</strong><br />
                    possessor fails to exercise reasonable care to eliminate the danger or otherwise proctect the children.</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Strict Liability </strong></p>
                    <p>D who engages in following three types of activities is STRICTLY LIABLE to any person who is actually and proximately caused the injury.</p>
                    <p>a. known, dangerous animal<br />
                        b. exotic animal (not commonly domesticated)<br />
                        c. ultra-hazardous activities that poses extreme risks to others.</p>
                    <p>Duty is presumed in above cases and injury is the breach.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;                      </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Rescuer Doctrine / Fireman's Rule </strong></p>
                    <p>a. D who creates perilous situation<br />
                        b. is liable for rescuer's injury<br />
                        c. exception is fireman if they they get injured in rescue.</p>
                    <p>A person who starts rescuing and then he must continue helping else be liable for the proximal caused worsening of injury.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under tort law a defendant who creates a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">perilous situation</strong>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">liable</strong>&nbsp;to all who are accidentally<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">injured coming to the rescue</strong>&nbsp;(except for professional rescuers; see the FIREMAN'S RULE) even though the rescuers who are injured are not in the ZONE OF DANGER created by the defendant's acts or injured by the dangers created.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">FIREMAN'S RULE:</strong>&nbsp;Under broadly adopted modern statutes defendants who create&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">dangerous situations</strong>&nbsp;that cause accidental injury to&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">professional rescuers</strong>&nbsp;like firemen are generally<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;not liable to them&nbsp;</strong>for negligence under the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">RESCUER DOCTRINE</strong>. These statutes are generally based on the view that professional rescuers both&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">assume the risks&nbsp;</strong>of their professions and are compensated for by insurance plans like the &quot;workman's compensation&quot; program.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Respondeat Superior </strong></p>
                    <p>a. employer/master is vicariously liable for employee/servant<br />
                        b. for tort committed within the scope of employment</p>
                    <p>frolic - minor diversion</p>
                    <p>detor - major diversion</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the doctrine of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">RESPONDEAT SUPERIOR</strong>&nbsp;an employer,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">master</strong>&nbsp;or principal is<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;vicariously liable</strong>&nbsp;for all torts committed by an employee, servant or agent, respectively, if the tort is committed within the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">scope of the employment</strong>&nbsp;or agency relationship.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Respondeat superior&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">does not apply</strong>&nbsp;to independent contractors.</p>                    <p>&nbsp;  </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Vicarious Liability of Joint Enterprise</strong></p>
                    <p>a. Each member of J.E is vicariously liable for<br />
                        b. tort committed by other member<br />
                        c. within the scope of enterprise relationship<br />
                        d. each member share equal benefit in joint enterprise</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under tort law each member of a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">JOINT ENTERPRISE</strong>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">vicariously liable</strong>&nbsp;for all torts committed by other members&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">within the scope</strong>&nbsp;of the enterprise relationship.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">A joint enterprise is one in which two or more parties&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">agree to work together</strong>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">mutual benefit&nbsp;</strong>and each shares equal rights of control over assets and activities.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Vicarious Liability of Independent Contractor</strong></p>
                    <p>a. D who hires independent contractor to perform delegable duties  <br />
                    b. is not vicariously liable for the torts committed by contractor<br />
                        c. they can only be liable for negligent selection or negligent entrustment.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under tort law defendant who hires an</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to perform duties that are not &quot;non-delegable&quot; by law is&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">NOT vicariously liable&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">for torts committed by the contractor and can only be&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">directly liable</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;because of&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">negligent selection or negligent entrustment&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">of the contractor by the defendant. An independent contractor is a person selected to provide labor services&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">without close and regular supervision</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Breach</strong></p>
                    <p>a. D did not exercise the degree of CARE;<br />
                        b. that a reasonable person would do in same circumstances;<br />
                        c. Standard of care is level of care based on experience and profession.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under tort law a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">BREACH</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;is the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">failure</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to exercise DUE CARE. The&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">standard of due care</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;is that level of caution a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">reasonably prudent person&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">would use in the same circumstance.</span></p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">Breach is brought using following methods:</strong></p>
                    <ol style="box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">
                        <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Negligence Per Se</li>
                        <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Res Ipsa Loquitur</li>
                        <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Violation of Standard Profession/Skills</li>
                        <li style="box-sizing: border-box;">Balance Test (Learned Hand Formula)</li>
                    </ol>                    </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Breach based on Res Ipsa Loquitor </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Negligence by someone (facts)<br />
                        b. defendant had control on events;<br />
                        c. plaintiff had no control on events;</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under the doctrine of&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">RES IPSA LOQUITUR</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;an&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">INFERENCE OF BREACH</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;exists if 1)&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">negligence</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;by someone is&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">implied</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;by the facts, 2) the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">defendant</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;had&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">control</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;of the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">event</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;or instrument that caused injury, and 3) the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">plaintiff</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;had&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">no control</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;over the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">event</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;or instrument causing injury.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Breach based on Negligence Per Se</strong> (See above) </p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Breach based on Balanced Test (Learned Hand Formula) </strong></p>
                    <p><strong>a. Risk</strong></p>
                    <p>Likelihood of Injury (x multiply) Gravity of Injury</p>
                    <p>Should be more than (to cause negligence) </p>
                    <p><strong>b. Justification   </strong></p>
                    <p>Burden of Prevention (+ plus) Social Utility </p>
                    <p><strong>likelihood</strong> of injury like <br />
                    12 year old can cross fence easily<br />
                        fence is 6', which can be easily crossed by 12 year old,<br />
                        Barbed wire is not very protective,<br />
                        Signs can be ignored by 12 year old boy<br />
                        so it is higly likely that boy can cross wire and get injured</p>
                    <p><strong>Gravity</strong> like<br />
                        Touching of live wire can cause grave injury</p>
                    <p><strong>Burden of prevention</strong> like<br />
                        higher fence should have been used<br />
                        more wires should have used</p>
                    <p><strong>Social Utility</strong> like<br />
                        utility of pole is need of commuity so it cannot be removed but can be made safe.                            </p>
                    <p><span >If Risk outweighs justification, there is negligence, and if justification outweighs risk, then there is no negligence. So based on above analysis of balance test, risk is more than justification so there is breach.</span></p>
                    <p >Using Hand formula and you have to figure out B, P, and L.</p>
                    <p >B: the burden of taking the precaution &mdash; in this case the working radio &mdash; is $100.</p>
                    <p >P: The&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">probability of harm if the precaution is not taken</strong>&nbsp;is 5 percent (or .05), which is multiplied by the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">gravity of harm&nbsp;</strong>(L) if an accident does occur, or $30,000.</p>
                    <p >Thus, .05 &times; 30,000 = $1,500. Once you compute this figure, and know that the precaution cost is $100.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Based on Negligent Entrustment </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Negligently entrust third parties <br />
                        b. with resources or authority<br />
                        c. directly liable for injuries</p>
                    <p><span >Under tort law defendants who NEGLIGENTLY ENTRUST&nbsp;</span><strong >third parties</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;with&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">resources</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;or authority are directly&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">liable</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;for&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">injuries actually and proximately caused</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;as a result.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Breach based on Professional Standard </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Level of care <br />
                    b. Which reasonable person would take<br />
                        c. based on professional standards</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under tort law a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">BREACH</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;is the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">failure</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to exercise DUE CARE. The&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">standard of due care</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;is that level of caution a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">reasonably prudent person&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">would use in the same circumstance.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Causation</strong></p>
                    <p>Actual and Proximate cause (see below)</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Actual Cause </strong></p>
                    <p>a. No injury but for the acts of defendant;<br />
                        b. or, 2 or more people negligent;<br />
                        c. no injury if no one has acted;<br />
                        d. cannot prove who's act causes injury;<br />
                        e. each is substantial factor in injury;</p>
                    <p>D's act caused or substantial cause of P's injury because it would not have happened but for D's act. </p>
                    <p><strong>But For</strong><br />
                    But for D's act, injury would not have occured. </p>
                    <p><strong>Substantial Factor</strong><br />
                    D's act may just be substantial cause among others, sole cause or concurrent cause with other person's act.                     </p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Proximate Cause </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Injury to plaintiff is<br />
                        b. so <strong>direct</strong>, <strong>natural</strong>, <strong>foreseeable</strong>;<br />
                        c. close in TIME and PLACE
                        <br />
                    d. from <strong>chain of causation</strong> of D's act<br />
                    e. <strong>unbroken</strong> by <strong>unforeseeable</strong> intervening events;<br />
                    f. law will impose the liability</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under tort law&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">PROXIMATE CAUSE</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;means that the injury suffered by the plaintiff was so&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">DIRECT, NATURA</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">L and&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">FORESEEABLE</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, so&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">close in time and place</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, resulting from a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">CHAIN OF CAUSATION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;begun by the defendant's acts,&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">unbroken</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;by&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">UNFORESEEABLE INTERVENING EVENTS</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;that the law will impose liability for the result.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Egg Shell Plaintiff </strong></p>
                    <p>a. D is negligent and causes injury to P<br />
                        b. pre-existing condition in P<br />
                        c. P is vulnerable to injry with no fault of the P<br />
                        d. D is liable for the injury.</p>
                    <p>D's aggravated the P's pre-existing condition and is liable for all the damages.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Harm</strong></p>
                    <p>a. P's harm must be physical injury or property damage,<br />
                    b. not economic damage or purely mental harm (NIED) </p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>General Damages </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Pain and Suffering</p>
                    <p>General damages are presumed to be existed, no need to prove it. </p>
                    <p><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">GENERAL</strong><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;damages are allowed for&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">pain and suffering</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Special Damages </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Out of pocket costs</p>
                    <p>Special damages are not presumed and must be proved. </p>
                    <p><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">SPECIAL damages</strong><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;are the plaintiff's</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;out-of-pocket costs</strong></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Contributory Negligence </strong></p>
                    <p>a. P acted <strong>negligently</strong><br />
                        b. P <strong>helped</strong> to cause the accident<br />
                        c. P is <strong>contributory negligent</strong> and <strong>bar</strong> to recovery.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under tort law&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">CONTRIBUTORY NEGLIGENCE</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;is a complete&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">bar to recovery</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;if the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">plaintiff</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;was&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">responsible</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;in any manner for their injury. It is a MINORITY VIEW rule, and the MAJORITY approach is&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">COMPARATIVE NEGLIGENCE</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;which just&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">reduces</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;the plaintiff's recovery based on the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">degree of fault&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">of the plaintiff. In some states a plaintiff that is over 50% at fault for her own injuries is completely barred from recovery.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Last Clear Chance </strong></p>
                    <p>a. D has last clear opportunity to avoid the accident. </p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Contributory Negligence often produces harsh results and many jurisdictions use the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">LAST CLEAR CHANCE DOCTRINE</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">allow</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">negligent</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;plaintiff to still&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">recover</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;where&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">if</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">defendant</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;had the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">last clear opportunity</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">avoid</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">accident</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Comparative Negligence </strong></p>
                    <p>a. P is negligent on certain percentage<br />
                        b. P is bar to recovery to reduced amount based on the % of negligence</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Assumption of Risks </strong></p>
                    <p>a. P deliberately put themselves at risk<br />
                        b. with full awareness of risk<br />
                        c. a conscious acceptance of the risk.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under tort law ASSUMPTION OF THE RISK is a complete&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">bar to recovery</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;for negligence if 1) plaintiffs&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">deliberately</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;put themselves at&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">risk</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;2) with</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;full awareness</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;of the risks and 3) a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">conscious acceptance&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">of the risks.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>NIED</strong></p>
                    <p>a. bystander<br />
                        b. emotional distress<br />
                        c. nexus between the negligent act and injury based on proximity in time, place and relationship.</p>
                    <p>Witnesses the negligent act and suffers mental distress.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under tort law, a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">BYSTANDER</strong>&nbsp;to an event may bring an action for&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">NEGLIGENT INFLICTION</strong>&nbsp;if they suffer severe emotional distress and there is a nexus between the negligent act and the injury based on a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">PROXIMITY IN TIME, PLACE and RELATIONSHIP</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">In some jurisdictions a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">physical manifestation of emotional distress</strong>&nbsp;must be shown.</p>                    <p>&nbsp;  </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>D. PRODUCTS LIABILITY </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Products Liability </strong></p>
                    <p>Prima facia case in Product's Liability</p>
                    <p>a. defendant manufactured, distributed or sold a defective product.<br />
                        b. the defect in product was the actual and proximate cause of the injury<br />
                        c. plaintiff sufferred damages.</p>
                    <p>Under <strong>product's liability</strong><br />
                        a. a person who <strong>places</strong> <br />
                        b. 
                        <strong>unreasonably dangerous</strong> product<br />
                        c. into the <strong>stream of commerce</strong><br />
                        d. may be <strong>liable</strong> for injury it caused.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Unreasonably Dangerous Product </strong></p>
                    <p>A product is unreasonably dangerous if:</p>
                    <p>a. it poses serious and<strong> likely dangers</strong>;<br />
                        b. could be reduced or <strong>eliminated easily</strong>;<br />
                        c.<strong> without damaging</strong> product <strong>utility</strong>;<br />
                        d. or product utility does not justify the dangers posed.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defect Types </strong></p>
                    <p>Three types of defects:<br />
                            <strong>a. manufacturing: </strong>(strict liability) a particular product is different from rest due to assemply, materials or parts. <br />
                            <strong>b. design: </strong>(negligence like approach) product designed as intended but creates unreasonable harm <br />
                        <strong>c. warranty:</strong> dangers, not apparent to customers, can be used to get economic damages.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>Five Theories </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Intentional</strong></p>
                    <p>a. manufacturer, distributor or seller<br />
                        b. knew that product would cause harm.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Breach of Express Warranty </strong></p>
                    <p>a. product is sold with express representations<br />
                        b. buyer relies on it<br />
                        c. representations are incorrect<br />
                        d. buyer is injured</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Breach of Implied Warranty </strong></p>
                    <p>a. product is unsafe for ordinary or intended use<br />
                        b. buyer relies on seller's expertise<br />
                        c. buyer is injured.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Negligence</strong></p>
                    <p>a. defendant has a duty <br />
                    b. not to place unreasonably dangerous goods<br />
                        c. into the stream of commerce<br />
                        d. plaintiff is foreseeable<br />
                        e. breach is not following duty <br />
                        f. breach actually and proximately caused injury
                    to plaintiff</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Strict Liability </strong></p>
                    <p>a. seller was commercial supplier<br />
                        b. product was unreasonably dangerous when it left defendant's control<br />
                        c. buyer is injured<br />
                        d. only non economic damages</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>E. DEFAMATION </strong></p>                    </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defamation</strong></p>
                    <p>a. <strong>False statement</strong> of material fact.<br />
                        b. <strong>Published</strong> to Others<br />
                        c. About <strong>Plaintiff</strong><br />
                        d. <strong>Causing</strong> damage to Reputation</p>                    </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Slander / Libel </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Slander or Oral Statement<br />
                    b. Libel or Written Statement</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Per Se / Per Quod </strong></p>
                    <p>Injury is presumed if it is libel per se or Slander per se.</p>
                    <p>Libel is always per se.</p>
                    <p>Slander per se is found when false statement alleges Club - criminal behavior, loathsome disease, Unchaste behvior, Improper Business practices.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;  </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defenses</strong></p>
                    <p>a. <strong>Consent</strong> of the Plaintiff (consent is complete defense) <br />
                        b. <strong>Truth</strong> (Truth is also a complete defense where element false is not matching) <br />
                        c. <strong>Privilege</strong> (see below) <br />
                        d. <strong>Absolute Privilege</strong> (judicial proceedings, between spouses, legislative sessions, comments made by federal officials, etc. <br />
                        e. <strong>Qualified Privilege: </strong>Reasonably believe it was true, or personal or professional interest, or share with same interest people. </p>
                    <p><strong>Many false statements are privileged.</strong><br />
                        To defend private interest, public interest, group interest.<br />
                        Does so without malice.<br />
                        In a reasonable manner.<br />
                        Calculated to defend the interest.<br />
                        Without unnecessary harming the plaintiff.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;                     </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>New York vs. Progeny </strong></p>
                    <p>Public figure plaintiff must prove malice. <br />
                    False statement was made with knowledge or<br />
                        Reckless disregard of its falseness</p>
                    <p><br />
                    </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Public Figure </strong></p>
                    <p>Is a person who has acted to put themselves in a public spotlight.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Public Concern </strong></p>
                    <p>Where matter is of public concern or where plaintiff seeks punitive damage, Plaintiff must prove atleast Negligence. </p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>Note: </strong><br />
                    Public Figure - actual malice<br />
                    Public Concern, public person - malice<br />
                    Public Concern, private person - negligence </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>F. INVASION OF PRIVACY (DIAL) </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Disclosure of Private Facts </strong></p>
                    <p>a. unreasonable public disclousre<br />
                        b. of private facts<br />
                        c. reasonable person would find it embarassing.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Intrusion upon seclusion</strong></p>
                    <p>a. unreasonable intrusion<br />
                        b. upon peace and solitude of a person.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;                     </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Appropriate of Likeness </strong></p>
                    <p>a. unauthorised use<br />
                    b. of name or likeness<br />
                        c. that implies endorsement of the product<br />
                        d. but not mere publication of names and photo.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>False Light </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Published False Portrayal<br />
                        b. that causes embarrassment or invonvience</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>G. NUISANCE </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"> <p><strong>Private Nuisance </strong></p>
                    <p>a. unreasonable interference<br />
                        b. with person's use and enjoyment<br />
                        c. of their own land.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Public Nuisance </strong></p>
                    <p>a. unreasonable interference <br />
                    b. with person's use and enjoyment<br />
                        c. of public resources</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Coming to the Nuisance</strong></p>
                    <p>a. plaintiff moved to location<br />
                        b. condition complained already existed</p>
                    <p>Defense in minority view, but in majority view, it is used in determining the damages.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;                  </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Remedies in Nuisance</strong></p>
                    <p>Monetary damage and Injunctive relief</p>
                    <p>a. Injunction is measure that prevents D from continuing the action<br />
                        b. that plaintiff seeks relief from</p>
                    <p>If nusiance is temporary, monetary damage measured by the loss of use of property for the period of nuisance will be adequate.</p>
                    <p>If nusiance is permanant, court can grant injunctive relief unless it cannot stop the nuisance because of social utility.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;In determining whether D conduct amounted to a public nuisance, the court will consider these factors: 1) the type of neighborhood, 2) the nature of the act; 3) the proximity of the act to the victims; 4) the frequency, 5) duration, 6) the timing of the act; 7) the extent of the damage that resulted.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;  </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>H. MISCELLANEOUS </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">Abuse of Process </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">Illegal Interference </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">Malicious Prosecuation </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">Fraud</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">Nondisclosure</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">Tort Restitution </td>
            </tr>
        </table></td>
        <td width="34%" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5">
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>A. Murder</strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Murder</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>a. Homicide</strong></p>
                    <p>Killing of <strong>one human</strong> being by <strong>another</strong>.</p>
                    <p><strong>                        b. Actual Cause</strong></p>
                    <p>But for Test: But for the act of D, the result would not have occured. </p>
                    <p><strong>c. Proximate Cause</strong></p>
                    <p>Proximate cause is direct and natural result of the act of defendant. </p>
                    <p><strong>d. Murder</strong></p>
                    <p>Unlawful homicide with malice aforethought. </p>
                    <p><strong>e. Malice Aforethought: </strong></p>
                    <p>i. Intent to kill, <br />
                        ii. 
                        Great bodily injury,<br />
                        iii. Felony Murder Rule, <br />
                        iv. 
                        Depraved Heart Theory (deliberate creation of risks, awareness of risks, conscious disregard of it)</p>
                    <p>Under common law, no degrees of murder, but under modern law, murder is divided into first and second degree.  </p>
                    <p><strong>f. Second Degree Murder</strong></p>
                    <p>If there is malice aforethought, then atleast the person will get second degree murder unless there is justification or excuse. He can first degree murder if he has additional fact patterns. </p>
                    <p><strong>g. First Degree Murder</strong></p>
                    <p>i. Willful, deliberate, premeditated murder <br />
                    ii. done by enumerated means like torture, poison, etc.<br />
                        iii. caused by commission of felony murder rule.</p>
                    <p><strong>Felony Murder Rule</strong></p>
                    <p>i. death caused during commission of dangerous felony like BARRKSS;<br />
                        ii. death during res gestae of the underlying felony;<br />
                        iii. res gestae is seq of events starting from first substantial step till defendant leaves the scene of crime.</p>
                    <p><br />
                    </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Voluntary Manslaughter </strong></p>
                    <p>a. d committed murder<br />
                        b. due to <strong>adequate provocation</strong> or improper self-defense<br />
                        c. d lost self control<br />
                        d. reasonable person would lose self control in same situation<br />
                        e. <strong>no cool off</strong> period.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Involuntary Manslaughter </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Unintentional homicide<br />
                        b. from gross negligence or recklessness or malum in se crime;</p>
                    <p><strong>gross negligence</strong>: is deliberate breach of pre-existing duty</p>
                    <p><strong>recklessness</strong> is deliberate creation of extreme risks.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under criminal law, Involuntary manslaughter is an&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">unintentional homicide</strong>&nbsp;resulting from&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">GROSS NEGLIGENCE</strong>,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">RECKLESSNESS</strong>&nbsp;or the commission of a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">MALUM IN SE</strong>&nbsp;crime insufficient to support the felony murder rule.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">GROSS (CRIMINAL) NEGLIGENCE is the deliberate&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">breach of a pre-existing duty to protect others</strong>&nbsp;from extreme risks, and RECKLESSNESS is the deliberate&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">creation of extreme risks</strong>&nbsp;to others.</p>                    <p>&nbsp;                      </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Redline Rule </strong></p>
                    <p>a. killing of accomplice<br />
                        b. other than accomplice<br />
                        c. during felony<br />
                        d. cannot be used as basis for felony murder rule.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the REDLINE RULE the killing of a criminal&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">accomplice by any party other than another criminal accomplice</strong>&nbsp;during the commisison of an inherently dangerous&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">felony</strong>&nbsp;can<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">not be used as basis for charging murder</strong>&nbsp;under the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">FELONY-MURDER RULE</strong>.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Assault</strong></p>
                    <p>a. <strong>acting with intention</strong> of causing<br />
                        b. a <strong>battery</strong> or else harmful or offensive touching</p>
                    <p>Victim must not be aware of the danger</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under CRIMINAL LAW an&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">ASSAULT&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">is the crime of acting with the intention of causing a battery or else to cause&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">apprehension of a battery</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">. The victim of the attempted battery does not have to be aware of the danger.&nbsp;</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;  </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Battery</strong></p>
                    <p>a. acting with intention of causing<br />
                        b. a touching of victim's person<br />
                        c. and causing a harmful or offensive touching</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under CRIMINAL LAW a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">BATTERY&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">is the crime of acting with the intention of causing a touching of a victim&rsquo;s person and causing a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">harmful or offensive touching</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Rape</strong></p>
                    <p>a. intentional act<br />
                        b. to have a sexual intercourse without consent<br />
                        c. causing actual penetration</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under common law RAPE was an</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;intentional act to have sexual intercourse</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;with a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">female without consent</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;causing&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">actual penetration</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, no matter how slight.</span> </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Kidnapping</strong></p>
                    <p>a. unlawful taking or confining of a person<br />
                        b. against their will</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">criminal law</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">KIDNAPPING&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">is the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">unlawful taking or confining</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;of a person</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;against their will</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>B. Inchoate Crime </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Attempt</strong></p>
                    <p>a. intent to commit a stated crime<br />
                        b. substantial step taken to do it</p>
                    <p><strong>substantial step:</strong><br />
                        act that brings defendant dangerously close to committing the intended crime.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under CRIMINAL LAW an ATTEMPTED CRIME is a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">SUBSTANTIAL STEP</strong>&nbsp;taken toward committing an INTENDED CRIME.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />
                    </p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">Attempted Crime?</strong></p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Two things to prove: 1)&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">intent</strong>&nbsp;to commit a stated crime, 2)&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">substantial step</strong>&nbsp;taken to do it.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;" />
                    </p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Nice Analysis of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">Attempted Arson</strong>?</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under criminal law, an attempted arson is a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">SUBSTANTIAL STEP</strong>&nbsp;taken with&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">INTENT</strong>&nbsp;to commit arson. A substantial step is an&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">ACT</strong>&nbsp;that brings the defendant&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">DANGEROUSLY CLOSE</strong>&nbsp;to committing the intended crime.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under common law,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">ARSON</strong>&nbsp;was the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">MALICIOUS BURNING</strong>&nbsp;of the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">DWELLING of ANOTHER</strong>. Malice for burning means wrongful intent. But modernly arson has been broadly extended to the malicious burning of almost any&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">STRUCTURE</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Here A acted with&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">INTENT</strong>&nbsp;to commit arson because he decided to &quot;set fire&quot; to the athletic equipment shed&quot;. That was not a dwelling, so he was not trying to commit common law arson. But it is a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">STRUCTURE</strong>&nbsp;because it is a &quot;shed&quot;. And he was acting with&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">MALICIOUS INTENT</strong>because he had no legal right to do this. So this would have been arson under the modern law.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">And A made a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">SUBSTANTIAL STEP</strong>&nbsp;toward committing his intended crime because he came&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">DANGEROUSLY CLOSE</strong>&nbsp;because he had &quot;matches&quot; and made &quot;severe tries&quot; to set the shed on fire.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Therefore A could be charged with attempted arson.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Solicitation</strong></p>
                    <p>a. urging another<br />
                        b. to commit a crime</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under CRIMINAL LAW a SOLICITATION is the crime of&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">urging another person</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to commit a crime.</span> <span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">The crime of SOLICITATION is complete as soon as the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">urging takes place</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">, whether the person urged commits the crime urged or not. But if the urged crime is committed the SOLICITATION&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">MERGES into the criminal result&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">and the person committing the solicitation becomes an ACCESSORY BEFORE THE FACT and VICARIOUSLY LIABLE for the crime based on accomplice theory.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Conspiracy</strong></p>
                    <p>a. agreement between 2 or more people<br />
                        b. to do an illegal act</p>
                    <p><strong>Modernly</strong><br />
                    a. overt act is required</p>
                    <p><strong>Pinkerton's rule:</strong><br />
                        a. member of conspiracy<br />
                        b. is vicariously liable<br />
                        c. for the crimes of co-conspirators<br />
                    d. if done within the scope of conspiration</p>
                    <p>i.e. crimes are foreseeable and in furtherance of the conspiracy goal.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under COMMON LAW the crime of CONSPIRACY was an<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;agreement between two or more people</strong>&nbsp;to work toward an illegal goal.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">MODERNLY an&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">OVERT ACT</strong>&nbsp;in furtherance of the conspiracy goal is often required in many Courts.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Further, under the PINKERTON RULE, a member of a conspiracy is VICARIOUSLY LIABLE for the criminal acts of co-conspirators done WITHIN THE SCOPE of the conspiracy goal. This means crimes that were 1)&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">foreseeable&nbsp;</strong>and 2) in&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">furtherance of the conspiracy goal</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Even if the illegal goal of the conspiracy is attained, the<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;CONSPIRACY DOES NOT MERGE</strong>&nbsp;into the criminal result, so each member can be convicted of both conspiracy and the other crimes committed during and within the scope of the conspiracy.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">And under the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">WHARTON RULE</strong>&nbsp;a conspiracy requires the participation of more people than the minimum number necessary to commit the criminal act.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">If a defendant joins a conspiracy<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;in progress</strong>&nbsp;most Courts hold they are not liable for previous crimes of the co-conspirators unless the joining defendant seeks to profit from those prior crimes.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">A conspiracy ends when the conspiracy goal is&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">ATTAINED or ABANDONED</strong>, and vicarious liability will no longer attach based on conspiracy theory. But it may still attach based on accomplice theory.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;                   </p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Accomplice Liability </strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Accomplice</strong><br />
                        a. a person who helps, aids, abets another person <br />
                        b. 
                    to commit a crime </p>
                    <p><strong>Liability</strong><br />
                    a. is liable for all subsequent crimes of co-felons<br />
                        b. that are direct and natural result of prior crimes.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">A person who commits or helps commit a crime is liable for all subsequent crimes by co-felons that are a direct and natural result of the prior crimes.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>C. Against Home </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Arson</strong></p>
                    <p>a. malicious burning<br />
                        b. of dwelling of another</p>
                    <p><strong>Modernly</strong><br />
                        a. any structure</p>
                    <p>Wrongful intent is required. </p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under common law ARSON was the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">malicious burning</strong>&nbsp;of the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">dwelling of another</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">MODERNLY arson is extended by statute to the burning of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">other structures</strong>. Malice for arson means that the burning must be done with&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">wrongful intent</strong>.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Burglary</strong></p>
                    <p>BEDONI</p>
                    <p>a. breaking<br />
                    b. entering<br />
                        c. dwelling<br />
                        d. 
                        of another<br />
                        e. at night time<br />
                        f. with intent to commit felony inside</p>
                    <p><strong>Constructive Breaking</strong><br />
                        a. entry made with trick, threat of violence, or help of conspirator</p>
                    <p><strong>Modernly</strong><br />
                        a. any structure<br />
                            b. any time<br />
                            c. larceny also in addition to felony<br />
                    d. trespassory entry </p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under COMMON LAW a BURGLARY was the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">breaking&nbsp;</strong>and&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">entering&nbsp;</strong>of the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">dwelling of another&nbsp;</strong>in the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">night&nbsp;</strong>with&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">intent to commit a felony</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Further, a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">CONSTRUCTIVE BREAKING</strong>&nbsp;would be found if entry was made by trick, threat of violence, or with the help of conspirator.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">MODERNLY burglary has been extended to almost any structure and all times of the day. If a larceny is not felony, it still supports a charge of burglary. And modernly a constructive breaking will be found if there is any TRESPASSORY ENTRY, an entry without permission, express or implied.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>D. Theft Crimes </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Larceny</strong></p>
                    <p>a. <strong>trespassory</strong> <br />
                        b. <strong>taking</strong><br />
                        c. <strong>carrying</strong> away <br />
                        d. the <strong>personal</strong> property<br />
                        e. of <strong>another</strong><br />
                        f. with <strong>intent</strong> to permanently deprive.</p>
                    <p>TTCPAI</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under common law LARCENY was the trespassory taking and carrying away of the personal property of another with intent to permanently deprive.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Where the possession was gained by misrepresentation it was called LARCENY BY TRICK.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Theft of property from a master or employer by a manager or high-level employee was generally embezzlement and not a larceny, unless the defendant got possession by misrepresentation, a larceny by trick. But theft of the same property by a servant or low-level employee was generally larceny, not embezzlement, unless the defendant took possession from a third party before deciding to steal it, and in that case it was embezzlement.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the RELATION BACK DOCTRINE some common law courts held that a theft of &quot;lost&quot; property by a person who initially intended to return it to the lawful owner was a larceny because a later decision to steal RELATED BACK to make the original taking unlawful. But other courts held this was embezzlement on the theory the original taking formed a &quot;constructive trust.&quot;</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Embezzlement</strong></p>
                    <p>a. <strong>trespassory</strong><br />
                        b. <strong>conversion</strong> of property<br />
                        c. by one <strong>entrusted with lawful possession</strong><br />
                        d. with <strong>intent</strong> to permenantly deprive </p>
                    <p>Theft by high level employee is embezzelement</p>
                    <p>Theft by low level employee is larceny.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under common law EMBEZZLEMENT was the crime of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">TRESPASSORY CONVERSION</strong>&nbsp;of the property of another by&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">one entrusted with lawful possession</strong>&nbsp;with&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">intent to permanently deprive</strong>&nbsp;or causing substantial risk of loss.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Further, the COMMON CARRIER DOCTRINE held that a common carrier such as a taxicab, bus or ship is entrusted with possession of passenger's property, including lost property, so a theft of passenger property by an employee of a common carrier was more often held to be EMBEZZLEMENT than larceny, even if the property was &quot;lost&quot;.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Larceny by trick </strong></p>
                    <p>a. Larceny but possession gained by misrepresentation</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Robbery</strong></p>
                    <p>a. larceny<br />
                        b. by use of force or fear<br />
                        c. to overcome the will of victim to resist </p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under CRIMINAL LAW a ROBBERY is a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">larceny</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;from a person by use of&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">force</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;or&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">fear</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to overcome the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">will of the victim to resist</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>False Pretenses </strong></p>
                    <p>a. misrepresentation of a fact<br />
                        b. to obtain the title of the property<br />
                        c. with intent to permenantly deprive</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under common law FALSE PRETENSES was the a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">MISREPRESENTATION of FACT</strong>&nbsp;to obtain&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">TITLE</strong>to the property of another with&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">intent&nbsp;</strong>to permanently deprive.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Receiving Stolen Property </strong></p>
                    <p>a. taking possession<br />
                        b. of stolen property<br />
                        c. knowningly it is stolen<br />
                        d. with intent to permenantly deprive</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under CRIMINAL LAW RECEIVING STOLEN PROPERTY is the crime of taking&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">possession</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;or control over&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">stolen personal property</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;while&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">knowing it has been stolen</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;with&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">intent</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to permanently deprive the lawful owner.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><strong>E. Defenses </strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Self Defense </strong></p>
                    <p>a. reasonable force to defend self</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under criminal law a defendant is privileged to use reasonable force as necessary for SELF-DEFENSE.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Consent</strong></p>
                    <p>a. consent must be<br />
                        b. <strong>informed</strong>, <strong>voluntary</strong><br />
                        c. with<strong> legal capacity</strong></p>
                    <p>not a defense to great bodily harm</p>
                    <p>is a defense to larceny, rape, battery, etc.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under CRIMINAL LAW consent is a defense to some crimes.[rape, larceny, battery - consent to a touching] The consent must be informed, voluntary and given by one with legal capacity. Further, consent is not a defense to an act that causes great bodily harm.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Others </strong></p>
                    <p>a. reasonable force<br />
                        b. to defend others<br />
                        c. who are not aggressors</p>
                    <p><strong>step in shoes</strong><br />
                        a. person step in shoes of aggressor and so no defense</p>
                    <p><strong>Reasonable test</strong><br />
                        a. person if reasonably believed that aggressor is defending, then it is a valid defense</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under CRIMINAL LAW a defendant is privileged to act with&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">reasonable forc</strong>e to&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">protect</strong>&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">others</strong>&nbsp;from an aggressor. Courts are split when a defendant mistakenly aids an aggressor. Some Courts say the defendant who mistakenly aids an aggressor STEPS-INTO-THE-SHOES of the aggressor and cannot claim any defense. Other Courts hold that a defendant can claim this defense if they acted on REASONABLE APPEARANCES</p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Defense of Property </strong></p>
                    <p>a. reasonable force<br />
                        b. to proctet own property or property of others</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under CRIMINAL LAW a defendant is privileged to use&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">reasonable</strong>, non-deadly force to&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">protect</strong>&nbsp;his own&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">property</strong>&nbsp;or the property of others from harm.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Mistake of Fact </strong></p>
                    <p>a. D did not have the necessary intent<br />
                        b. because he either did not intend to commit the criminal act (General Intent)<br />
                        c. or to cause the criminal result (specific intent)
</p>
                    <p>mistake of fact is complete defense if it negates criminal intent</p>
                    <p><strong>General Intent Crime</strong><br />
                        a. only reasonable mistake can negate the criminal intent</p>
                    <p><strong>Specific Intent Crime</strong><br />
                        a. negate criminal intent whether reasonable or not</p>
                    <p><strong>General Intent crimes</strong> like battery, rape, arson, involuntary manslaughter, murders that are not wilful and deliberate are general intent crime.</p>
                    <p>all others are <strong>specific intent crimes</strong></p>
                    <p>mistake of fact is no defense to attempt if criminal intent is proven and mistake merely prevented an otherwise criminal act. </p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under CRIMINAL LAW a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">MISTAKE OF FACT</strong>&nbsp;is a complete defense if it negates implied criminal intent. For&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">GENERAL INTENT</strong>&nbsp;crimes only a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">REASONABLE</strong>&nbsp;mistake can negate criminal intent. For&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">SPECIFIC INTENT</strong>&nbsp;crimes&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">ANY MISTAKE OF FACT</strong>&nbsp;may negate criminal intent whether reasonable or not. Battery, rape, arson, involuntary manslaughter and murders that are not willful and deliberate are general intent crimes. All other crimes are&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">SPECIFIC INTENT</strong>&nbsp;crimes.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">A&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">REASONABLE MISTAKE OF FACT</strong>&nbsp;is one that a reasonable person would have made in the same situation.&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">VOLUNTARY INTOXICATION</strong>&nbsp;never makes an otherwise unreasonable mistake reasonable.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">A MISTAKE OF FACT is no defense to a charge of&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">ATTEMPT</strong>&nbsp;if criminal intent is proven and the mistake merely prevented an otherwise criminal act.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Mistake of Law </strong></p>
                    <p>Mistake of law is not a defense</p>
                    <p>a. mistake of law about the <strong>legality of act</strong>;<br />
                        b. <strong>does not alter</strong> the <strong>legality</strong> of act;</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under CRIMINAL LAW, A MISTAKE OF LAW about the legality of an act does not alter the legality of the act.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">If the defendant commits a criminal act believing it is legal, it is still an illegal act. Likewise, if the defendant commits a legal act believing it is illegal, it is still a legal act.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp;                     </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Legal Impossibility </strong></p>
                    <p>it is a valid defense because attempted crime is not a crime. </p>
                    <p>a. attempted act is not an attempted crime<br />
                        b. even if there is criminal intent</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under CRIMINAL LAW,</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;LEGAL IMPOSSIBILITY</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;means that an attempted act is not an attempted crime, even if there was criminal intent, when the attempted crime is a legal impossibility at the time of the first substantial step.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Factual Impossibility </strong></p>
                    <p>a. there is criminal intent<br />
                        b. act taken by D is not a substantial step toward crime <br />
                        c. because it will <strong>not produce criminal result</strong></p>
                    <p>like killing a dead person, will be charged with attempted crime</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under CRIMINAL LAW,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">FACTUAL IMPOSSIBILITY</strong>&nbsp;is a defense that the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">act actually done</strong>&nbsp;by the defendant was&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">NOT A SUBSTANTIAL STEP</strong>&nbsp;toward commission of any crime, despite&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">criminal intent</strong>, because the&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">act taken could never produce a criminal result</strong>.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp;  </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">Intoxication</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Insanity </strong></p>
                    <p><strong>a. M'Naughten Rule</strong>: unable to appreciate the nature and quality of his acts or know they are wrong.<br />
                        <strong>b. Irresistible Impulse:</strong> unable to control their acts, even if they know their act is wrong.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under criminal law INSANITY is a defense that negates criminal intent. Under the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">M'NAUGHTEN RULE</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;a person is insane if a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">disease of the mind</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;so impairs their reasoning that they are&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">unable to appreciate&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">the nature and quality of their acts or to</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;know that they are wrong</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">. Under the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">IRRESISTIBLE IMPULSE&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">theory a person may raise the defense of insanity if they are unable to control their acts, even if they know the act is wrong.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Infancy</strong></p>
                    <p>a. Conclusive presumption that child <strong>below 7 years</strong> cannot form criminal intent. <br />
                    b. rebuttable presumption that child between age of <strong>7 and 14</strong> could not form criminal intent.<br />
                    c. child <strong>above age 14 </strong>can form criminal intent.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under the&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">COMMON LAW</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;there as a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">CONCLUSIVE PRESUMPTION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;that a child&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">under the age of seven</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;was&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">unable</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to form&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">CRIMINAL INTENT</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">. There was a&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">REBUTTABLE PRESUMPTION</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;that a child between&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">7 and 14</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;could&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">not</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;form criminal intent, and a child over the age of&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">14</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;was believed to be able to form criminal intent.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Necessity</strong></p>
                    <p>a. defense of necessity may be raised to certain crimes;<br />
                        b. it is nothing but <strong>self defense</strong>, <strong>defense of others</strong>, <strong>defense of property</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under CRIMINAL LAW a defense of NECESSITY may be raised to certain crimes.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">This defense is really nothing more than self-defense, defense of others, or defense of property.</p>
                    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Duress</strong></p>
                    <p>a. duress is defense of all crimes <strong>except</strong> murder.</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under CRIMINAL LAW a defense may be raised to crimes, EXCEPT MURDER, that the criminal act was the result of DURESS.</span> </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Withdrawal</strong></p>
                    <p>a. person who is member of conspiracy is not liable for crime of co-conspirators if<br />
                        b. they <strong>give notice</strong> that they are abandoning the conspiracy<br />
                        c. try to <strong>stop pursuing</strong> of the criminal goal.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">CRIMINAL LAW</strong>,&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">WITHDRAWAL</strong>&nbsp;is a defense that defendants who were members of a&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">CONSPIRACY</strong>&nbsp;are not liable for crimes committed by co-conspirators AFTER the defendants</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">1) give the other co-conspirators&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">NOTICE</strong>&nbsp;that they are abandoning the conspiracy and</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">2) the defendants&nbsp;<strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700;">TRY TO STOP</strong>&nbsp;the co-conspirators from continuing pursuing the conspiracy goal.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Prevention of Crime </strong></p>
                    <p>a. reasonable force<br />
                        b. to prevent crime<br />
                        c. in their presense</p>
                    <p><span style="font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; white-space:normal; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; display:inline !important; float:none; font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">Under CRIMINAL LAW a defendant is privileged to&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">act with reasonable force</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;to&nbsp;</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">PREVENT SERIOUS CRIMES</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">&nbsp;being committed</span><strong style="box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: 700; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">&nbsp;in their presence</strong><span style="font-family:verdana; font-size:12px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-style:normal; font-weight:400; ">.</span></p>
                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top"><p><strong>Entrapment</strong></p>
                    <p>a. defense if criminal intent was due to <strong>improper police behavior</strong><br />
                        b. <strong>no defense </strong>if defendant was <strong>pre-disposed</strong>.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under CRIMINAL LAW entrapment is a defense if criminal intent was the product of improper police behavior.</p>
                    <p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Under the majority view entrapment is no defense if the defendant was predisposed to commit the crime. Under another minority view entrapment is a defense if police conduct was outrageous and instigated the crime, even though the defendant was predisposed.</p>                    <p>&nbsp; </p></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td valign="top">&nbsp;</td>
            </tr>
        </table></td>
    </tr>
</table>
</body>
